The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 21 December is 12,300 (1,423.6 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 16 December, there were 1,448 new confirmed cases (167.6 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 09 December, there were 746 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 94% (702 extra cases).
